    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3650" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπι-τίθημι</span></b> , fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιθήσω</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπέθηκα</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπίθες</span>,
          opt. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιθείη</span>, 2 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-θεῖτε</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">put</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">place
            to</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">upon, add</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            7.364</span></i>; of putting food on the table, <i><span class="en">Od. 1.140</span></i>; a veil on the head, <i><span class="en">Od.
            5.314</span></i>; the cover on a quiver, <i><span class="en">Od.
            9.314</span></i>; a stone against a doorway, <i><span class="en">Od. 9.243</span></i>; and regularly of ‘closing’ doors (cf. ‘pull the
          door <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">to</span>’), <i><span class="en">Il. 14.169</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 22.157</span></i>, cf. <i><span class="en">Il. 5.751</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            8.395</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 11.525</span></i>; metaph.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θωήν</span>, ‘impose’ a penalty, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.192</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; μύ̄θῳ τέλος</span>, ‘give fulfilment,’
            <i><span class="en">Il. 19.107</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
